cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on active learning in the context of deep learning and image classification, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): This is the most likely category, as the paper deals with active learning and semi-supervised learning, which are both subfields of machine learning. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper specifically focuses on image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Active learning and semi-supervised learning are both relevant to artificial intelligence, which makes this category a likely fit. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language): While not as likely as the previous categories, the paper does deal with natural language processing in the context of image classification. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on deep learning, which is a subfield of neural computing.
